6:
They made your oars from the oaks of Bashan;
\q they made your decks out of cypress wood from Cyprus, and they overlaid them with ivory.
\q

8:
Those who were living in Sidon and Arvad were your rowers;
\q the sages of Tyre were within you; they were your pilots.
\q

26:
Your rowers have brought you into vast seas;
\q the eastern wind has broken you in the middle of them.
\q

29:
All those who handle oars will come down from their ships;
\q mariners and every sailor of the sea will stand on the land.
\q
